      "title": "[Open Culture] How Fritz Lang’s Metropolis Created the Blueprint for Modern Science Fiction (1927)",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<img src=\"https://cdn8.openculture.com/2026/02/26224101/scifiblueprint-1024x576.jpg\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nA vast, miserable proletariat squanders its days in meaningless toil. Society is under the control of ultra-wealthy business magnates. In order to pacify the underclass, the ruling class pins its hopes on a technological solution: artificial intelligence. Welcome to the year 2026, as envisioned in Fritz Lang’s&#160;Metropolis. When the film premiered, not long after 1926 [&#8230;]",
